COPS in Hammanskraal, north of Pretoria dug up a body and took it to the mortuary on Thursday. A 61-year-old man was reported missing by his wife two weeks ago.Police spokesman Captain Kay Makhubela said a man walked into the police station on Wednesday and told the cops that he was haunted by a bad deed.He claimed he received a call from a friend who wanted help with carrying rubbish to a bushy area on New Year&rsquo;s Eve. Makhubela said: &ldquo;He told the police that when he arrived at his friend&rsquo;s place, he found him with a woman preparing to carry a zinc bath with a plastic bag inside.&ldquo;The man said he helped them carry the bath, but he got tired and left the others on the way to the bush. &ldquo;He claimed he didn&rsquo;t know there was a body in the plastic bag until the following day.&ldquo;He said he helped the woman and the man to bury the body and was threatened not to tell anyone about it.&rdquo;Makhubela said a case of murder was opened and no one has been arrested yet. &ldquo;The informer might be charged for defeating the ends of justice,&rdquo; he said.The police are trying to find the friend and the dead man&rsquo;s wife.